    "# Phasespace"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c5929fe4-eb4a-44c4-8a50-1164ef5f5d80",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This is an example of plotting phase space distributions.\n",
    "First, create a simple line, a tracker and a particle set:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "5dcde2bb-196e-4872-a5da-0881e7bfd2f2",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "mystnb": {
     "code_prompt_show": "Show imports"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2\n",
    "\n",
    "import xtrack as xt\n",
    "import xpart as xp\n",
    "import xplt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(43543557)\n",
    "\n",
    "xplt.apply_style()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "8c9de8e8-6892-4afd-a9e7-d0530f0e28fa",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "mystnb": {
     "code_prompt_show": "Show line generation code"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "remove-output",
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Compiling ContextCpu kernels...\n",
      "Done compiling ContextCpu kernels.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "## Generate a simple 6-fold symmetric FODO lattice\n",
    "\n",
    "n = 6  # number of sections\n",
    "elements = {\n",
    "    \"QF\": xt.Multipole(length=0.3, knl=[0, +0.63]),\n",
    "    \"QD\": xt.Multipole(length=0.3, knl=[0, -0.48]),\n",
    "    \"MU\": xt.Multipole(length=0.5, knl=[np.pi / n], hxl=[np.pi / n]),\n",
    "}\n",
    "parts = {\n",
    "    \"a\": [\n",
    "        xt.Node(0.7, \"QF\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(1.4, \"MU\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.1, \"QD\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.8, \"MU\"),\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    \"b\": [\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.2, \"MU\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.9, \"QD\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(3.6, \"MU\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(4.3, \"QF\"),\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "}\n",
    "nodes = [xt.Node(5.0 * i, \"a\" if i % 2 else \"b\", name=f\"S{i+1}\") for i in range(n)]\n",
    "\n",
    "line = xt.Line.from_sequence(\n",
    "    nodes, length=5.0 * n, sequences=parts, elements=elements, auto_reorder=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "line = line.cycle(4)\n",
    "line.particle_ref = xp.Particles()\n",
    "line.build_tracker();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "dc01b34c-73dc-4767-b108-82ddc490f565",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "mystnb": {
     "code_prompt_show": "Show particle generation code"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Compiling ContextCpu kernels...\n",
      "Done compiling ContextCpu kernels.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "## Generate particles\n",
    "nparticles = int(1e4)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Transverse distribution (gaussian)\n",
    "norm_emitt_x = 4e-6  # normalized 1-sigma emittance in m*rad (=beta*gamma*emitt_x)\n",
    "norm_emitt_y = 1e-6  # normalized 1-sigma emittance in m*rad (=beta*gamma*emitt_y)\n",
    "x, px = xp.generate_2D_gaussian(nparticles)\n",
    "y, py = xp.generate_2D_gaussian(nparticles)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Longitudinal distribution (coasting beam)\n",
    "rel_momentum_spread = 1e-4  # relative momentum spread ( P/p0 - 1 )\n",
    "zeta = line.get_length() * np.random.uniform(-0.5, 0.5, nparticles)\n",
    "delta = rel_momentum_spread * xp.generate_2D_gaussian(nparticles)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "particles = line.build_particles(\n",
    "    x_norm=x,\n",
    "    px_norm=px,\n",
    "    nemitt_x=norm_emitt_x,\n",
    "    y_norm=y,\n",
    "    py_norm=py,\n",
    "    nemitt_y=norm_emitt_y,\n",
    "    method=\"4d\",  # for twiss (default is 6d, won't work without a cavity)\n",
    "    zeta=zeta,\n",
    "    delta=delta,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9bf582c7-be6f-40b0-afa2-7cecc617a8e6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Default phasespace plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "714252cd-9c38-4574-844a-ee10a3e09235",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Create a default {class}`PhasespacePlot <xplt.phasespace.PhaseSpacePlot>`:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "ce664506-dfe9-44ff-a7a9-4035d1041d5b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x400 with 9 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(particles)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0d78a9cb-57cb-46ce-9de4-b8b6da19453f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1D Histograms can also be plotted using {class}`ParticleHistogramPlot <xplt.particles.ParticleHistogramPlot>`.  \n",
    "By default the particle count per bin is plotted, here we use `kind=` to plot the charge instead:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "a3abd124-b988-49c6-ab12-8bf2357ce22a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.ParticleHistogramPlot(\n",
    "    \"x\", particles, kind=\"charge\", bin_width=1e-4, figsize=(4, 3)\n",
    ")  # bin_width is in data units (m)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ebcf8fc2-2782-4dca-9759-67a714090ee4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c12848a-3156-4b43-8019-23a5916c56ae",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Customisation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ace4bf8c-3038-47d3-a6b6-b174726a2008",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Use the parameter `kind` to specify what is plotted as a comma separated list of pairs `a-b`.\n",
    "The properties `a` and `b` can be any property of a particle such as `x`, `px`, `y`, `delta`, `zeta`, `Jx`, `Θy` etc. Note that `zeta` is the absolute value, while `zeta_wrapped` is the wrapped value in range (-circumference/2 ; +circumference/2).\n",
    "See [Default properties](/examples/concepts.ipynb#default-properties) for a complete list of default properties and refer to [Adding custom data properties](/examples/concepts.ipynb#adding-custom-data-properties) for an explanation of how to add custom ones."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ff48d777-aa08-4292-8a89-68e3dca4ab17",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "```{tip}\n",
    "The `kind=` parameter accepts abbreviations for common pairs, e.g. `x` for `x-px`, `z` for `zeta-delta` or `Y` for `Y-Py`\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7736b0c1-e185-4275-816b-9161bea4adda",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here we also add some ellipses to indicate standard deviation and percentiles, disable the default projections, and use a scatter plot with some transparency.\n",
    "See {class}`PhasespacePlot <xplt.phasespace.PhaseSpacePlot>` for details."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "6ab49e52-0bdd-4f69-98ce-3f67bf0b90ac",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(\n",
    "    particles,\n",
    "    mask=particles.particle_id < 1e4,\n",
    "    kind=\"x,y,x-y\",\n",
    "    plot=\"scatter\",  # using a scatter plot instead of a 2D histogram\n",
    "    scatter_kwargs=dict(alpha=0.2),  # scatter plot with semi-transparent color\n",
    "    projections=False,  # No projections onto axes\n",
    "    display_units=dict(p=\"urad\"),  # p as shorthand for px and py\n",
    "    mean=True,  # show mean cross for all\n",
    "    std=[True, None, True],  # show std ellipse for first and last\n",
    "    percentiles=[[90], [70, 80, 90], None],  # show some percentile ellipses\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot.ax[2].set(title=\"Transverse profile\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cc8182b8-2b3e-46a2-aa81-647072bf874a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```{tip}\n",
    "Most parameters accept a list of values to specify different values for each subplot\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1af42e36-17e0-4d57-8545-4149b724b57c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Normalized coordinates"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "964ab22d-02b3-4125-8148-0ede575d9b9a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Calculate twiss parameters for normalization:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "377e1dfc-ece8-4857-a124-36c455a4e36b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tw = line.twiss(\n",
    "    method=\"4d\",\n",
    "    at_elements=np.unique(particles.at_element),  # twiss at location of particles\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7889000f-7655-4ba4-9e2e-f3f7fdc3a9e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use uppercase letters for normalized coordinates (`X` is the shorthand for `X-Px`):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "4482f529-0328-4f03-b972-01a2a4f7e0f8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(particles, kind=\"X,Y-Py\", twiss=tw, std=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "## Color by 3rd coordinate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "8fb272c1-ec97-4fd1-83cb-9808461d8e08",

   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(\n",
    "    particles,\n",
    "    \"x,y,zeta_wrapped-delta\",\n",
    "    color=\"Θx,Jy,t\",  # <-- color by value\n",
    "    cmap=\"petroff_cyclic\",\n",
    "    cbar_loc=\"inside upper right\",\n",
    "    twiss=tw,\n",
    "    grid=False,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8120900c-2409-4628-9d00-e3a486199206",

    "## Monitor data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "320f9204-cb78-419f-8ff3-03af549b3d9f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Track the particle for a couple of turns:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "4bd939ea-f16a-4214-b479-0888e66a8f84",

   "source": [
    "line.track(particles, num_turns=100, turn_by_turn_monitor=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a60358fe-9863-4b03-bcc9-8fd0b2084f27",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use `mask=` to select a subset of the data to plot, e.g. a single turn:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "dfb1c55d-ccd9-4ea4-97d8-dea1fbb368b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x400 with 9 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(\n",
    "    line.record_last_track,\n",
    "    mask=(slice(None), 83),  # select all particles and turn 83\n",
    "    mean=(1, 1, 0),\n",
    "    std=(1, 1, 0),\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot.fig.suptitle(\"Particle distribution for a single turn\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "30fcc924-fc26-4e9f-a118-4ce6c2a840ac",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "900755bd-06f7-4000-855a-dbc52d3e1c53",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use `masks=` to set a different mask for each subplot:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "6e2c1242-a412-4e8b-b0e7-696953ac283c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(\n",
    "    line.record_last_track,\n",
    "    kind=\"y,y\",\n",
    "    titles=(\"First turn\", \"Last turn\"),\n",
    "    sharex=\"all\",\n",
    "    sharey=\"all\",\n",
    "    masks=[\n",
    "        (slice(500), 0),\n",
    "        (slice(500), -1),\n",
    "    ],  # select 500 particles at first and last turn\n",
    "    projections=\"x\",\n",
    "    mean=True,\n",
    "    std=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot.ax[1].set(ylabel=None);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "73aa08c5-fbaa-41d9-baf5-887b9f1427d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plot the trace of some particles:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "03821f67-c90f-48c7-a541-f7be4259b4f6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(\n",
    "    line.record_last_track,\n",
    "    mask=([17, 18, 21], slice(None)),  # select particles 17,18,21 and all turns\n",
    "    projections=False,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7fef80ea-727a-49a3-afc2-6d8da64e3abf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plot the trace of some particles as distinct plots on the same axis:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "da9ba0db-231f-42bc-bb80-a777be7d0f22",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 7 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ax = None\n",
    "for particle_i in (17, 18, 21):\n",
    "    plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(\n",
    "        line.record_last_track,\n",
    "        mask=(particle_i, slice(None)),  # select particle i and all turns\n",
    "        scatter_kwargs=dict(label=f\"#{particle_i}\"),\n",
    "        kind=\"X\",\n",
    "        twiss=tw,\n",
    "        titles=(\"Trace of single particles\",),\n",
    "        ax=ax,  # draw on same plot as before\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    ax = plot.ax\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend(title=\"Particle\");"
   ]
  },
  {
